    <item>
      <title>AWS Integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/aws-integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/aws-integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;aws-integration-requirements&#34;&gt;AWS Integration Requirements  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#aws-integration-requirements&#34; title=&#34;AWS Integration Requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To create an Integration for AWS, you need to &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-sec-cred-types.html#iam-user-name-and-password&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;configure an AWS IAM user&lt;/a&gt; with the following roles:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1f0da68de8&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1f0da68de8&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;ec2:*Instance*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;ec2:*Tags*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;ec2:*Instance*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;ec2:*Tags*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In addition, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to copy and save the following &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-sec-cred-types.html#access-keys-and-secret-access-keys&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;AWS security credentials&lt;/a&gt; to use when creating an AWS Integration:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;access key ID&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;secret access key ID&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;add-an-aws-integration&#34;&gt;Add an AWS Integration  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#add-an-aws-integration&#34; title=&#34;Add an AWS Integration&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To create an AWS Integration, take the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>BIG-IP Integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/big-ip-self-service/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/big-ip-self-service/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can use F5 NGINX Controller to configure a BIG-IP cluster to work with NGINX instances in your app delivery infrastructure. By using NGINX Controller, you can configure your NGINX instances as part of your BIG-IP device&amp;rsquo;s virtual servers and server pools.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;NGINX Controller uses the &lt;a href=&#34;https://clouddocs.f5.com/products/extensions/f5-appsvcs-extension/latest/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;F5 Application Services 3 Extension (AS3) package&lt;/a&gt; to communicate with a BIG-IP cluster. This means NGINX Controller works with any BIG-IP version that supports AS3.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Datadog Integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/datadog-integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/datadog-integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;datadog-integration-requirements&#34;&gt;Datadog Integration Requirements  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#datadog-integration-requirements&#34; title=&#34;Datadog Integration Requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;F5 NGINX Controller sends data to the Datadog API; NGINX Controller does not use an agent. Datadog requires that NGINX Controller present an access token with the data to authenticate the service.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Log into the &lt;a href=&#34;https://app.datadoghq.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Datadog web interface&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;On the navigation menu, select &lt;strong&gt;Integrations&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;strong&gt;APIs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Expand the &lt;strong&gt;API Keys&lt;/strong&gt; pane.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;If you already have a key available, you can use it. If you don&amp;rsquo;t, or if you want to create &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.datadoghq.com/account_management/api-app-keys/#using-multiple-api-keys&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;a different key&lt;/a&gt;, you can do so by &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.datadoghq.com/account_management/api-app-keys/#add-a-key&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;typing a key name and clicking &lt;strong&gt;Create API key&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Copy and save the API key you want to use. &lt;strong&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ll configure NGINX Controller with this value later&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Datadog restricts the creation of API keys to Admin users. You may need to contact your administrator to get a new key.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;add-a-datadog-integration&#34;&gt;Add a Datadog Integration  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#add-a-datadog-integration&#34; title=&#34;Add a Datadog Integration&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Take the following steps to create an Integration for Datadog:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>OTLP Integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/otlp-integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/otlp-integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;otlp-integration-requirements&#34;&gt;OTLP Integration Requirements  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#otlp-integration-requirements&#34; title=&#34;OTLP Integration Requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Confirm that your OpenTelemetry Collector server meets the following configuration requirements:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;transport-protocol&#34;&gt;Transport protocol  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#transport-protocol&#34; title=&#34;Transport protocol&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The OpenTelemetry Collector server should be configured to allow the following OTLP receiver protocols:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;HTTP  - for unencrypted connections.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;HTTPS - for encrypted connections. Certificate validation and mutual TLS are &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; supported.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;gRPC  - for unencrypted gRPC connections.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;gRPC + TLS - for encrypted gRPC connections. Certificate validation and mutual TLS are &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; supported.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;otlp-protocol&#34;&gt;OTLP protocol  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#otlp-protocol&#34; title=&#34;OTLP protocol&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The server should expose the OTLP receiver.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Syslog Integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/syslog-integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/syslog-integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;syslog-integration-requirements&#34;&gt;Syslog Integration Requirements  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#syslog-integration-requirements&#34; title=&#34;Syslog Integration Requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Confirm that your Syslog server meets the following requirements:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;network-protocol&#34;&gt;Network protocol  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#network-protocol&#34; title=&#34;Network protocol&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The syslog server should be able to receive data via one of the following protocols:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;TCP  - for unencrypted connections.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;TLS  - for encrypted connections. Validation of the Certificate Authority (CA) and mutual TLS are currently &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; supported.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;syslog-format&#34;&gt;Syslog Format  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#syslog-format&#34; title=&#34;Syslog Format&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The forwarder produces &lt;a href=&#34;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RFC-5424&lt;/a&gt;-compliant messages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Splunk Integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/splunk-integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-controller/platform/integrations/splunk-integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;splunk-integration-requirements&#34;&gt;Splunk Integration Requirements  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#splunk-integration-requirements&#34; title=&#34;Splunk Integration Requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;(Optional) If you want to forward metrics and you haven&amp;rsquo;t already created a Splunk Index for metrics, take the steps below to add one. You can do the same for events, although you could also use the existing, default &amp;ldquo;main&amp;rdquo; index.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Open the Splunk web interface and log in.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Settings&lt;/strong&gt;, then select &lt;strong&gt;Indexes&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;New Index&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Add a Name.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;For the &lt;em&gt;Index Data Type&lt;/em&gt;, select &lt;strong&gt;Metrics&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Events&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Save&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;set-up-splunk-to-monitor-data&#34;&gt;Set up Splunk to Monitor Data  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#set-up-splunk-to-monitor-data&#34; title=&#34;Set up Splunk to Monitor Data&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Open the Splunk web interface and log in.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;On the Explore Splunk Enterprise menu, select &lt;strong&gt;Add Data&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Monitor&lt;/strong&gt; as the data method.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;On the Add Data &lt;em&gt;Select Source&lt;/em&gt; page, select &lt;strong&gt;HTTP Event Collector&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Add a Name.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Add a Description.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Next&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;On the Add Data &lt;em&gt;Input Settings&lt;/em&gt; page, select one or more of the available Splunk Indexes with the appropriate &lt;em&gt;Index Data Type&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Review&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;On the summary page, copy and save the token value. &lt;strong&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ll configure F5 NGINX Controller with this value later&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;add-a-splunk-integration&#34;&gt;Add a Splunk Integration  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#add-a-splunk-integration&#34; title=&#34;Add a Splunk Integration&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Take the following steps to create an Integration for Splunk:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
